{
  "texts": [
    "We use OpenAI's APIs to access its latest version, i.e., gpt-3.5-turbo-0613.• LLaMA [50]: A family of multilingual large language models ranging from 7B to 65B in parameter size, trained from various open-source datasets of up to 1.4 trillion tokens, where 4.5% are code from Github.",
    "We include three versions of 7B/13B/33B for experiments.• CodeGen [41]: A collection of language models trained on up to 354.7 billion English tokens and 222.5 billion code tokens.",
    "It also has diverse sizes in parameters ranging from 350M to 16.1B.",
    "During the experiment, we use codegen-6B-multi.• TransCoder [46]: It is an unsupervised machine translation-based transpiler pre-trained with cross-lingual language modeling, denoising auto-encoding, and back-translation.",
    "As such, a vast amount of monolingual samples can be leveraged for training."
  ]
}